# Plan: Add release adoption/health data to existing commands (#463)

## Context

Issue [#463](https://github.com/getsentry/cli/issues/463) requests release adoption and health
metrics (crash-free rate, adoption %, session counts) in the CLI.

**Origin/main already has a full `release` command group** with 11 files:
`list`, `view`, `create`, `delete`, `deploy`, `deploys`, `finalize`, `parse`,
`propose-version`, `set-commits`, plus `index.ts`.

**What's missing**: The existing `list` and `view` commands don't request or display health data.
The API module (`src/lib/api/releases.ts`) never passes `health=1` or `adoptionStages=1`. The
`OrgReleaseResponse` SDK type already includes `projects[].healthData` fields — they just come
back as `null`/absent because we don't ask for them.

**Branch state**: We're on `feat/mutate-command-helpers` (3 local commits). Need a new branch
from `origin/main`.

## Gap Analysis

| What exists | What's missing |
|-------------|----------------|
| `listReleasesPaginated` — no `health` param | Pass `health=1` to get adoption data per project |
| `getRelease` — no `query` param at all | Pass `health`, `adoptionStages`, `healthStatsPeriod` |
| List table: VERSION, STATUS, CREATED, RELEASED, COMMITS, DEPLOYS | ADOPTION and CRASH-FREE columns |
| View detail: basic metadata KV table | Per-project health breakdown section |
| No sort by health metrics | `--sort` with `crash_free_sessions`, `crash_free_users`, `sessions`, `users` |

